WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified standard reference for ISO/IEC 6048‑1, the JPEG AI
learning‑based image compression standard. It defines the autoencoder
architecture, the rate‑distortion training objective, and the bitstream
syntax for AI‑compressed still images.

WHY IT EXISTS
JPEG AI achieves up to 60% bitrate reduction over JPEG 2000 at equivalent
quality. GIOP must specify the reference decode pipeline to ensure
consistent colour reproduction from JPEG AI files.

HOW IT WORKS
An autoencoder (CNN/Transformer) compresses the image to a latent
representation, quantised and entropy‑coded. A decoder reconstructs
the image. The training loss includes perceptual metrics.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- Next‑generation still image compression
- GIOP archival and delivery.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers implementing JPEG AI codecs; archivists.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Defines the neural compression pipeline within GIOP, ensuring that
decoded JPEG AI images match the original ACES2065‑1 reference.

KEY FORMULAS

1. Rate‑Distortion Loss (training)
   L = D + λ * R
   where D = perceptual distortion (LPIPS + L1), R = estimated bitrate
   from entropy model.
   λ controls the compression/quality trade‑off.

2. Autoencoder Architecture
   Encoder: y = f_enc(x; θ_enc)  (x = input image in ACES linear)
   Quantised: ŷ = round(y – μ) + μ  (with learned bias μ)
   Decoder: x̂ = f_dec(ŷ; θ_dec)

3. Entropy Coding
   Probability model P(ŷ|context) used for arithmetic coding.

